text: Nthatisi Mota (born 12 April 2000) is a South African water polo player and coach. She competed for the South Africa women's national water polo team in the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. She played for Hotchkiss School. == References == Category:2000 births Category:Living people Category:South African water polo players Category:South African water polo coaches
